name: Disney World
description: Enjoy the happiest place on earth right from your home with a virtual trip to Disney World

name: Hike to Lanikai Pillboxes
description: Experience the warm Hawaiian sunrise on a virtual hike up to the Lanikai Pillboxes in Kailua, O'ahu

name: Walking in raining Tokyo
description: Walking starts in Kabukicho, Tokyo during a light thunderstorm in the evening. Binaural sounds of the residential side of Tokyo mixed with the sounds of thunder and rain hitting the umbrella.

name: Walking in the Rain in Manhattan
description: Evening walk in Midtown New York City in the rain.

name: Sunset in Gyeongju, Korea and Woljeonggyo Bridge
description: Quiet evening in Gyeongju and Woljeonggyo Bridge.

name: Catacombs of Paris
description: Explore this authentic, spooky, labyrinth of underground tunnels consecrated in 1786. Let's wander together through this 20-metre-deep maze which contains the bones of millions of Parisians.

name: A morning in London
description: Morning walk through some of my favorite secret spots in London. Lots of breathtaking views and hidden gems. This tour is only available during Spring time.

name: Sunrise in Maasai Mara, Kenya
description: Start your day with this beautiful scenery from an African natural reserve park. A true experience!

name: Travelling Riverside Blues
description: A canoe trip along Paraguay River in Pantanal, Brazil. Calm and full of native life.

name: Basque by Bike
description: Explore the Basque history and quirky charm of San Sebastián. Cycle along beaches, rivers, battlefields, and bays with a savvy guide, passing by aristocratic palaces and avant garde pinxto bars along the way. With a relaxed pace and the flexibility to stop often, It's a great way to get acquainted with San Sebastián’s contrasting historic highlights and modern vibe.

name: Visiting Pacific Science Center
description: Walking starts in the Space Needle base and follows through Pacific Science Center as I cross it on my way to buy bread. You will be able to see lots of cultural attractions like the Museum of Pop Culture and the Chihuly Garden and Glass museum, but only from the outside since they're all close during COVID season. At least you won't need to wear a mask, but I will surely do :)
